         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/11/81. ¶  ¶ Just a few mosses, dear Mr Mitten; you shall have lots of them hereafter, as I have a collector in the field. Dr C. Mueller is also anxious to have mosses from me. How can it be arranged...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.11.07a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Mitten</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Letters to W Mitten, 1848-1905, f. 208.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/11/81.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Just a few mosses, dear Mr Mitten; you shall have lots of them hereafter, as I have a collector in the field. Dr C. Mueller is also anxious to have mosses from me. How can it be arranged, that you are both supplied, without clashing? in the publication of any novelties? </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you could look over the msc. moss list or supplement early what is printed from Hampe,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Hampe’s list of Australian mosses, published as one of the appendices to vol. 11 of M’s <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta,</seg> pp. 45-69.</p>
               </note> I should be greatly beholden to you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
